2026-05-16 08:46:09 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #5 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Compute percentage of samples failing swimming standard (Enterococcus <=104 CFU/100mL is meeting) at Boston Harbor beaches with positive 1-Day Rain within 24h prior. Need total failed samples and failed samples with 1-Day Rain >0. Use all Boston harbor beach datasheet CSVs and union them; handle multiple sub-areas by taking all Enterococcus columns and corresponding Tag columns plus 1-Day Rain for each row.", "code": "import pandas as pd\nimport re\nfrom io import StringIO\n\ns3_prefix='s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-8/files/'\nfiles=[\n 'constitution_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'pleasure_bay_and_castle_island_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'city_point_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'm_street_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'carson_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'malibu_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'tenean_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'wollaston_beach_datasheet.csv'\n]\n\n# helper to load from s3\nimport fsspec, json\n\ndef read_s3_csv(name):\n    uri=s3_prefix+name\n    with fsspec.open(uri,'rb') as f:\n        data=f.read()\n    return pd.read_csv(StringIO(data.decode('utf-8')))\n\nall_failed=0\nall_failed_rain=0\n\nthreshold=104\n\nfor fn in files:\n    df=read_s3_csv(fn)\n    # identify 1-Day Rain column\n    day_col=[c for c in df.columns if '1-Day Rain' in c][0]\n    rain=df[day_col]\n    rain_pos=rain.astype(float)>0\n\n    # find all Enterococcus columns (may repeat per location)\n    enter_cols=[c for c in df.columns if 'Enterococcus' in str(c)]\n\n    # For each Enterococcus column, determine counts; cells may be '<' or '' strings like '<,10'.\n    # In CSV preview, there is also a Tag column paired with Enterococcus counts.\n    # We'll parse numeric from Enterococcus column values; if blank or NaN -> ignore sample.\n    for ec in enter_cols:\n        vals=df[ec]\n        # numeric extraction\n        num=pd.to_numeric(vals.astype(str).str.extract(r'(-?\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?)')[0], errors='coerce')\n        valid=num.notna()\n        # meeting swimming standard if <=104; failed if >104\n        failed=(valid) & (num>threshold)\n        all_failed += failed.sum()\n        all_failed_rain += (failed & rain_pos).sum()\n\npct=all_failed_rain/all_failed*100 if all_failed else float('nan')\nprint(all_failed, all_failed_rain, pct)\nprint(round(pct,2))\n"}) [toolUseId=call_U2TxPViD7rJCWcbTTdK14Q1g]
